# 
Shanghai's new daily casees soared to 27,719 according to data released on April 14, bringing total infections in the Chinese megacity to about 280,000 since March 1.
Residents in low-risk areas with no infections in the past 14 days can move around within their compound.
The number of new cases are still high, and risk will magnify if crowds gather, even in those low-risk zones.
The highest-risk zones remain sealed off, with resident not allowed to leave their homes.
Shanghai police have also banned cars from the roads. Only vehicles involved in pandemic prevention or transporting people in medical neeed are allowed.
On April 12, authorities warned that anyone who violates lockdown rules will be dealt with strictly.
Those who violate the provisions of the notice will be dealt wiith in strict accordance with the law by public security organs. -- Statement by Shanghai police department.


















