- Man occupies someone else’s train seat in China, but beats passengers when confronted.
This man who occupied someone else's vented his anger after being asked to move. 撒气、发火
When the passenger who booked the seat asked him to move, he refused to give the seat up and stood up to lay hands on the passenger. 动手
The man stayed in the seat even when the police arrived.
He was detained for 5 days. 拘留
The argument triggered anger online. 引起愤怒
How shameless is he to beat others when he's the one occupying the wrong seat? 不要脸
He should be put on the blacklist.



- Flight attendant subdues passenger after she ‘deliberately coughed’ at staff in China.制伏
This woman was restrained by flight attendants after she deliberately coughed at one.
控制
After waiting for 7 hours for a coronavirus check, she vented her anger, coughing at a woman attendant.
Other staff came and pressed her into her seat.
The flight had landed in Shanghai from Bangkok.
Shanghai customs said the plane's passengers had to be checked because some had transferred from Iran.
The woman's behavior divided opinion online.引起分歧
Why did she humiliate our nation? 给我们国家丢人
This is too humiliating. Must punish and blacklist her.
I would also be angry if i needed to wait for 7 hours.
Is it appropriate for attendants to violently restrain her? Let the authorities investigate.






